Explination
-> This method is a more refined and efficient way of a writting an 
if/else statement that involves a boolean. The method, "calculate_bonus", 
takes an integer and a boolean decided by the users input, and gives two 
gives a response to two different circumstances. The 'bonus's value is 
tested with the use of the '?' and that is when the system is provided two 
different responses based one what 'bonus's value. In this case that 
happens to be '(slary / 2)' and 0.


def calculate_bonus(salary, bonus)
  bonus ? (salary / 2): 0
end

puts calculate_bonus(2800, true)
puts calculate_bonus(1000, false)

